  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators administered a randomized controlled trial (RCT) through random assignment
      of children with ADHD into three different groups to compare the effects of cognitive-motor
      rehabilitation, immediate release methylphenidate, and an active control on the executive
      functioning, learning, and behavioral symptoms of children with ADHD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
